<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFDABA1AFCF0FE8EFC52FE44" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDABA1AFCF0FE8EFC52FE44" blockId="59.[813,1452,317,501]" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDABA1AFCF0FE8EFC0AFEE4" bold="true" box="[813,903,317,341]" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Biology</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFDABA1AFC47FE8EFB38FEE4" authorityName="Ng, Rani &amp; Nandan" authorityYear="2017" box="[922,1205,317,341]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Pseudosesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabrum">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDABA1AFC47FE8EFB38FEE4" box="[922,1205,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Pseudosesarma glabrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is semi-terrestrial in habits, occurring in the intertidal mixed mangrove forests of Aroor in the 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDABA1AFC3EFECEFBBCFE24" box="[995,1073,381,405]" name="India" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Cochin</collectingCountry>
estuary, 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFDABA1AFB46FECEFB6BFE24" box="[1179,1254,381,405]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Kerala</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDABA1AFB29FECEFAA2FE24" box="[1268,1327,381,405]" name="India" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">India</collectingCountry>
. Sympatric sesarmids include 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFDABA1AFC24FE2DFA21FE04" authority="(Latreille, 1803)" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1017,1452,413,437]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Parasesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plicatum">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDABA1AFC24FE2DFB62FE04" box="[1017,1263,413,437]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Parasesarma plicatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDABA1AFADDFE2EFA29FE04" author="Latreille" box="[1280,1444,413,437]" firstAuthor="Latreille" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" refId="ref71225" refString="Latreille PA (1803) Histoire naturelle, generale et particuliere des Crustaces et des Insectes. Ouvrage faisant suite aux oeuvres de Leclerc de Buffon, et partie du cours complet d'histoire naturelle redige par C. S. Sonnini, membre de plusieurs societes savantes. Vol. 5. F. Dufart, Paris, 468 pp." type="book" year="1803">Latreille, 1803</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFDABA1AFC86FE0DFC56FE44" authority="(Henderson, 1893) (Ng et al., 2017 a: 269)" authorityName="Ng et al." authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Henderson" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Neosarmatium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malabaricum">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDABA1AFC86FE0DFB03FE64" box="[859,1166,445,469]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Neosarmatium malabaricum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDABA1AFB40FE0EFAD5FE64" author="Henderson" box="[1181,1368,445,469]" firstAuthor="Henderson" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" pagination="325 - 458" refId="ref70011" refString="Henderson JR (1893) A contribution to Indian carcinology. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, Series 2, Zoology, 5 (10): 325 - 458, pls. 36 - 40." type="journal article" year="1893">Henderson, 1893</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDABA1AFAB3FE0EFC5EFE44" author="Ng" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ng" page="269" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" pagination="263 - 270" refId="ref73970" refString="Ng PKL, Rani V &amp; Nandan B (2017 a) A new species of Pseudosesarma Serene &amp; Soh, 1970 (Crustacea: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) from Cochin in southwest India. Zootaxa, 4311 (2), 263 - 270." type="journal article" year="2017" yearSuffix="a">Ng et al., 2017a: 269</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="89A6C9CBFFDABA1AFCF0FDAEFB02FD24" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFDABA1AFCF0FDAEFB02FD24" blockId="59.[812,1452,541,661]" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFDABA1AFCF0FDAEFC39FD84" bold="true" box="[813,948,541,565]" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Distribution</emphasis>
. The species was described from northern 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFDABA1AFABBFDAEFA21FD84" box="[1382,1452,541,565]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Kerala</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDABA1AFCE9FD8EFC67FDE4" author="Ng" box="[820,1002,573,597]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ng" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" pagination="263 - 270" refId="ref73970" refString="Ng PKL, Rani V &amp; Nandan B (2017 a) A new species of Pseudosesarma Serene &amp; Soh, 1970 (Crustacea: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) from Cochin in southwest India. Zootaxa, 4311 (2), 263 - 270." type="journal article" year="2017" yearSuffix="a">Ng et al., 2017a</bibRefCitation>
) but has since been found in other parts of 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFDABA1AFC96FDEEFC41FDC4" box="[843,972,605,629]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Kerala state</collectingRegion>
as well as in 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFDABA1AFBB9FDEEFB5FFDC4" box="[1124,1234,605,629]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="037854A2FFDABA1AFAD4FDEEFA03FDC4" box="[1289,1422,605,629]" country="India" name="Maharashtra" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">Maharashtra</collectingRegion>
in western 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFDABA1AFC57FDCEFC4CFD24" box="[906,961,637,661]" name="India" pageId="59" pageNumber="950">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFDABA1AFC0CFDCEFB09FD24" author="Pati" box="[977,1156,637,661]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Pati" pageId="59" pageNumber="950" pagination="139 - 146" refId="ref74629" refString="Pati SK, Sujila PS &amp; Sudha Devi AR (2020) Crab out of its shell: multiple records of the sesarmid crab, Pseudosesarma glabrum Ng, Rani &amp; Bijoy Nandan, 2017 (Decapoda: Brachyura: Sesarmidae), confirm species' wide distribution along the west coast of India. In: Nandan SB, Priyaja P &amp; Jayachandran PR (eds.) Frontiers in Benthic Science. Cochin University of Science and Technology, Kochi, India. Pp. 139 - 146." type="book chapter" year="2020">Pati et al., 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
